  "issue_title": "Completions modify os.Args",
  "issue_body": "I'm trying to workaround https://github.com/spf13/cobra/issues/1877 by inspecting `os.Args` by hand. In some cases cobra accidentally inserts `--` into `os.Args`.\n\nMinimal example:\n```go\npackage main\n\nimport (\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\n\t\"github.com/spf13/cobra\"\n)\n\nfunc main() {\n\tcmd := &cobra.Command{\n\t\tTraverseChildren: true,\n\t\tValidArgsFunction: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string, toComplete string) ([]cobra.Completion, cobra.ShellCompDirective) {\n\t\t\tcobra.CompErrorln(strings.Join(os.Args[1:], \", \"))\n\t\t\treturn nil, cobra.ShellCompDirectiveDefault\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\tif err := cmd.Execute(); err != nil {\n\t\tpanic(err)\n\t}\n}\n\n```\n\nExpected behaviour:\n```console\n$ go run . __complete x\n[Debug] [Error] __complete, x\n:0\nCompletion ended with directive: ShellCompDirectiveDefault\n```\n\nActual behaviour:\n```console\n$ go run . __complete x\n[Debug] [Error] __complete, --\n:0\nCompletion ended with directive: ShellCompDirectiveDefault\n```",
  "merged_at": "2026-04-24T20:41:58Z",
